# IPTV Guide UI (Prevue / TV Guide Channel)

Visual references: `cursor_dev_files/visual_inspo/Guide_Channel/`. Aim for a **1990s cable TV Guide Channel** feel — scrolling grid, channel logos, time blocks, current-program highlight.

## Layout principles

- Size everything with `root.sh` / `root.sw`; mind CRT overscan (safe margins ~12.5% like other modules).
- Use app theme colors from `Main.qml` (`root.primaryColor`, `accentColor`, etc.) unless `guide_theme` overrides.
- Channel logos from M3U `tvg-logo` / XMLTV `<icon>`; cache images locally in the data dir.
- Show channel number (`tvg-chno`) + name; programme title, sub-title, time range.
- Time axis: align programme blocks to start/stop from XMLTV; scroll horizontally through the schedule.

## Guide modes

| Mode | Behavior |
|---|---|
| **Passive** | Auto-scroll like a broadcast Guide Channel; minimal input (exit only, or OK to pause scroll) |
| **Interactive** | D-pad moves focus across channel rows and time slots; Enter tunes channel |

Implement both behind a `guide_mode` setting; share the same data model.

## Remote navigation

Required keys on every guide screen:

- **Up/Down** — change channel row (interactive) or speed scroll (passive)
- **Left/Right** — move time focus or scroll timeline
- **Enter** — tune selected channel → navigate to `Player.qml`
- **Escape / Backspace** — `goBack()`

Channel list (`Channels.qml`) can be a simpler vertical `ListView` as an alternate entry point.

## Channel transitions (analog style)

When changing channels from the guide or a channel-up/down action:

1. Brief QML overlay (static/snow/fade) **before** calling `mpvController.loadAndPlay` with the new URL.
2. Keep transition duration short (~300–800 ms) so tuning feels snappy on Pi 4.
3. Do not block the UI thread on network I/O during the effect.

## Weather Channel (future)

References: `cursor_dev_files/visual_inspo/Weather_Channel/`. Possible approaches:

- Dedicated `Weather.qml` view in the module router
- RetroCast integration or a custom QML template with local/API weather data
- Same remote-nav and sizing rules as the guide

## Reuse

- `import Components` → `AppBar` where a title bar fits (channel list); full-screen guide may omit it.
- Do not duplicate `MpvController` logic in QML — playback stays in `Player.qml`.
